istic conceptions of moral duty. The volume begins with a philosophical exploration of theories of loyalty, both Eastern and Western, then moves to examine several problematic situations in which loyalty is often a factor: partisan politics, the armed forces, and lawyer-client relationships. A fair and balanced analysis from a wide range of disciplinary and normative viewpoints, Loyalty infuses new life into an oft-tread avenue of scholarly inquiry. Contributors: Ryan K. Balot, Paul O. Carrese, Yasmin Dawood, Bernard Gert, Kathleen M. Higgins, Sanford Levinson, Daniel Markovits, Lynn Mather, Russell Muirhead, Nancy Sherman, Paul Woodruff  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aLoyalty. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBalot, Ryan K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarrese, Paul O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDawood, yasmin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGert, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiggins, Kathleen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevinson, Sanford V., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLevinson, Sanford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarkovits, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMather, Lynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuirhead, Russell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParker, Joel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSherman, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoodruff, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoodruff, Paul, eed